§ Main results ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $(x_n)_{n ∈ 𝗡}$ and $(y_n)_{n ∈ 𝗡}$ be two limits with
    $x_0$ and $y_0$ in $𝗥$. ⦉

  ‖ Then the sequence $(s_n)$ defined by $s_n = x_n + y_n$
    converges to the limit $x_0+ y_0$ and the sequence $m_n =
    x_ny_n$ converges to the limit $x_0y_0$.
    † ⦊
      ‖ Future editions will include the account. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
